Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt all but 2 tablespoons chocolate chips. Whisk together sweetened condensed milk, eggs, water, orange peel (optional) and melted chocolate chips. Stir bread into chocolate mixture and let stand 1 to 2 minutes. Spoon bread mixture into lightly buttered 13x9-inch baking dish. Dot top with butter. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven and sprinkle with reserved chocolate chips. Serve warm with Caramel Sauce (optional). Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.